---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" path="/about">
  <article class="wrap article">
    <header class="head">
      <div class="eyebrow mono">About this notebook</div>
      <h1>A developer's second brain.</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>knowbase</strong> is my living engineering notebook. It is where
        I write down what I am learning and building across software,
        infrastructure, and AI. It is not a diary. It is a knowledge base:
        notes, patterns, gotchas, and technical decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>Why it is built this way</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Files, not a database.</strong> Every note is Markdown in the
          repository. Versioned, mine, with no vendor lock-in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Astro.</strong> Static output, strong Core Web Vitals, and no
          unnecessary JavaScript.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>TinaCMS.</strong> A comfortable writing UI that also works from
          a phone, while every change still lands as a commit in the repo.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GitHub Pages.</strong> Hosting straight from the repository.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What you will find here</h2>
      <p>
        Rust, Go, distributed systems, Kubernetes and networking, databases, and
        observability, along with LLMs, agents, RAG, and practical AI work. The
        notes are written first for my future self. If they help someone else,
        even better.
      </p>

      <hr />
      <p class="mono small">
        Stack: Astro, TinaCMS, GitHub Pages. Code open, content mine.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .article {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding-top: 48px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .head {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 720;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--heading);
    margin: 12px 0 0;
  }
  .small {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }
</style>
